title: For Sale:  SMITH & WESSON ~ MODEL 50 '.38 CHIEFS SPECIAL TARGET' Very Scarce EXCELLENT ... .38 SPECIAL
postcontent:
Here's a hard-to-find Smith & Wesson revolver that was made in very limited numbers and was never officially cataloged! This is a Model 50 ".38 Chief's Special Target". Similar to the famous Model 36 Chief's Special but made with target sights. This revolver is built on the square butt J-frame with three screws, chambers the .38 Special, and has a five-shot cylinder. It wears a 2-inch barrel with tall serrated ramp front sight and fully adjustable rear sight. Overall condition is excellent. The original bright blue finish rates about 98% with a few handling marks, a couple of tiny blemishes on the bottom of the trigger guard, a small ding to the left edge of the front sight, and the usual cylinder turn line. The hammer and trigger both show bright case colors. The factory Magna stocks are in excellent condition, free of cracks or chips, and a serial numbered to match the revolver. The mechanics are in perfect working order with good timing and lock-up. The bore is likewise excellent with sharp, bright rifling. It comes in the original box which numbers to the gun and includes the cleaning kit and warranty card.
Produced between 1955-1975, total production is believed to be 2136 guns counting all the different variations. This revolver belongs to a group that were shipped in 1973. Most of the Chief's Special Target revolvers were actually marked "MOD.36" (or unmarked) in the crane recess while those marked "MOD.50" (like this example) are more scarce. A nice find for the S&W collector!

Buyer pays $20.00 shipping.

This translates to figuring out how to make cheaper and cheaper guns but keep the price the same. For my money I dont want a gun that is being made cheaper than it was a year ago.
